melist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/conveyal/r5\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">202</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":202,\"repo\":\"conveyal/r5\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A Java-based routing engine developed by Conveyal for multimodal (transit/bike/walk/car) networks. It currently plans many trips over a time window for scenario planning and analytics purposes. A related R wrapper package (<a href=\"https://github.com/ipeaGIT/r5r/\">r5r</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ipeaGIT/r5r/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">112</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":112,\"repo\":\"ipeaGIT/r5r\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) is developed independently by IPEA. See also the performance comparison from Higgins et al. (2022), linked below.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-02-16T20:39:20.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Academic papers</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://doi.org/10.5198/jtlu.2022.2012\">Higgins et al. - \"Calculating place-based transit accessibility: Methods, tools and algorithmic dependence\" (2022)</a> - Compares software tools for calculating accessibility by walking and public transit including ArcGIS Pro, Emme, R5R, and OpenTripPlanner.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-02-16T20:39:20.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"shuaibiyy/awesome-terraform","categoryHTML":"<h2>Boilerplates</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.kubestack.com\">Terraform GitOps Framework</a> - Everything you need to build reliable automation for AKS, EKS and GKE Kubernetes clusters in one free and open-source framework.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-02-16T20:36:41.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"shuaibiyy/awesome-terraform","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials and Blog Posts</h2><h3>How-To</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nufailtd/terraform-budget-gcp\">Google Cloud Platform for 10$ a month using terraform</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nufailtd/terraform-budget-gcp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">22</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":22,\"repo\":\"nufailtd/terraform-budget-gcp\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Shows how to use terraform to create a secure Google Kubernetes Cluster, Google Cloud Run Services and other infrastructure elements for less than <a href=\"https://nufailtd.github.io/budget-gcp/\">10$</a> a month.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-02-16T20:35:34.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"shuaibiyy/awesome-terraform","categoryHTML":"<h2>Providers</h2><h3>Vendor supported providers</h3>","itemH